<item>
            <title>[SOLR-5616] Make grouping code use response builder needDocList</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5616</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now the grouping code does this to check if it needs to generate a docList for grouped results:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (rb.doHighlights || rb.isDebug() || params.getBool(MoreLikeThisParams.MLT, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;) ){
...
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this is ugly because any new component that needs a doclist, from grouped results, will need to modify QueryComponent to add a check to this if. Ideally this should just use the rb.isNeedDocList() flag...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Coincidentally this boolean is really never used at for non-grouped results it always gets generated..&lt;/p&gt;</description>
